[Indistinct conversation]

06:49.585 --> 06:51.301
KIM: Ah, here he is.

06:51.336 --> 06:52.335
HOWARD: Oh, great.

06:52.387 --> 06:53.587
Jimmy, right on time. Good to see you.

06:53.589 --> 06:56.606
Hello, Howard. Hey. Hi.

06:56.659 --> 06:58.325
James McGill, Clifford Main.

06:58.377 --> 07:00.627
Just "Jimmy." And it's a
pleasure to meet you, Clifford.

07:00.663 --> 07:03.547
Likewise. We know all about
your work on Sandpiper.

07:03.582 --> 07:04.882
Well, it's a group effort.

07:04.917 --> 07:06.550
I mean, the folks at HHM

07:06.585 --> 07:08.385
are just knocking it out of the park.

07:08.421 --> 07:10.421
Well, you know, the case
wouldn't exist without you.

07:10.473 --> 07:11.555
Absolutely.

07:11.590 --> 07:12.973
Once you get him on your team,

07:13.008 --> 07:14.892
you'll know why I call him "Charlie Hustle."

07:14.927 --> 07:16.643
Jimmy, these are my associates...

07:16.679 --> 07:19.430
Brian Archuleta and Erin Brill.

07:19.482 --> 07:21.231
- Nice to meet you both.
- It's great to meet you.

07:21.267 --> 07:22.733
I hate to do this,

07:22.768 --> 07:24.902
but, um, could I borrow
Ms. Wexler for a moment?

07:24.937 --> 07:27.187
If you will excuse us?

07:27.239 --> 07:28.272
[Clears throat] Pardon me.

07:28.324 --> 07:30.190
[Chuckles]

07:34.113 --> 07:35.279
What's going on?

07:35.331 --> 07:36.580
I just, um [clears throat]

07:36.615 --> 07:38.198
Listen, here's the thing.

07:38.250 --> 07:42.252
If I take this job,
does that mean the two of us...

07:42.288 --> 07:44.922
I mean, uh...

07:44.957 --> 07:46.707
Does it mean, uh...

07:46.759 --> 07:49.176
What? What... What the hell is this?

07:49.211 --> 07:52.930
If I take this job today,
with Davis and Main

07:52.965 --> 07:56.633
[clears throat] does
that mean that you and me...

07:56.685 --> 07:59.887
Is this... Is this gonna happen?

08:05.811 --> 08:08.779
Jimmy, I...

08:11.283 --> 08:14.651
I...

08:14.703 --> 08:17.287
[Sighs]

08:17.323 --> 08:20.657
One thing has absolutely
nothing to do with the other.

08:21.794 --> 08:23.293
Nothing at all.

08:23.329 --> 08:24.728
No.

08:24.763 --> 08:28.131
Of course not. Why would it?

08:28.167 --> 08:30.584
Great. [Sighs]

08:33.820 --> 08:35.520
Uh, sorry about that.

08:35.613 --> 08:38.380
Listen, I just want to say
thank you, sincerely,

08:38.414 --> 08:39.548
For your interest in me.

08:39.582 --> 08:41.316
It's an honor to be considered,

08:41.352 --> 08:43.552
But at this time... At this time...

08:43.587 --> 08:47.156
Um, I'm gonna have to take
myself out of the running.

08:47.191 --> 08:48.757
Thanks.

08:48.792 --> 08:49.925
Thank you, Howard.

08:49.960 --> 08:52.461
Uh, Jimmy?

08:55.266 --> 08:56.999
[brakes screech]

08:57.456 --> 08:58.689
Mike: Well, that was quick.

08:58.742 --> 08:59.741
No charge.

08:59.776 --> 09:01.409
Help me out here.

09:01.444 --> 09:02.677
Did I dream it,

09:02.712 --> 09:08.349
Or did I have $1,600,000
on my desk in cash?

09:08.385 --> 09:10.919
No one on god's green earth
knew we had it.

09:10.954 --> 09:12.754
We could've split it 50/50.

09:12.789 --> 09:16.391
We could've gone home
with $800,000... each!

09:16.426 --> 09:18.893
Tax-free!

09:18.929 --> 09:20.361
Your point being?

09:20.397 --> 09:22.096
Why didn't we?

09:22.132 --> 09:26.067
I remember you saying something
about doing the right thing.

09:26.102 --> 09:28.369
You want to know why
I didn't take that money?

09:28.405 --> 09:30.405
Is that what you're asking?

09:30.440 --> 09:32.207
Yeah, that's what I'm asking.

09:32.242 --> 09:35.543
Me, personally, I was hired to do a job.

09:35.579 --> 09:36.911
I did it.

09:36.947 --> 09:38.613
That's as far as it goes.

09:38.648 --> 09:40.281
Yeah.

09:40.317 --> 09:43.117
Well, I know what stopped me.

09:43.153 --> 09:44.686
And you know what?

09:44.721 --> 09:47.455
It's never stopping me again.

09:47.490 --> 09:49.991
[engine revs]

09:51.061 --> 09:53.127
[to the tune of "Smoke on the Water"]
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh ♪

09:53.163 --> 09:55.563
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh-mnh ♪

09:55.599 --> 09:57.699
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh ♪

09:57.734 --> 09:59.901
♪ mnh, mnh ♪

09:59.936 --> 10:01.069
♪ mnh, mnh ♪

10:01.104 --> 10:02.470
[tires screech, brakes squeal]

10:02.505 --> 10:04.205
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh ♪

10:04.241 --> 10:06.674
[engine shuts off]

10:06.710 --> 10:08.743
♪ duh, duh, duh ♪

10:08.778 --> 10:11.012
♪ duh, duh, duh-duh ♪

10:11.047 --> 10:13.214
[humming]

10:13.250 --> 10:14.549
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh ♪

10:14.650 --> 10:16.750
Chao cac co, ladies! Chao cac co!

10:16.785 --> 10:18.652
Mrs. Nguyen, it's a beautiful day out there.

10:18.687 --> 10:20.253
You should get out of
this place once in a while.

10:20.289 --> 10:21.988
You know, throw a frisbee, have some fun.

10:22.024 --> 10:23.590
I have a business to run.

10:23.625 --> 10:26.259
Uh, no. The business is running you.

10:26.295 --> 10:29.095
Listen to me. You'll thank me later.

10:29.131 --> 10:32.332
[man singing in Vietnamese over radio]

10:32.367 --> 10:35.302
Cucumber water for customer only.

10:35.337 --> 10:36.670
[sighs]

10:36.705 --> 10:38.438
[women conversing in Vietnamese]

10:43.612 --> 10:45.845
[conversations stop]

10:50.719 --> 10:52.586
[chuckles]

10:52.621 --> 10:56.489
[conversations resume]

10:56.525 --> 10:59.192
[speaks Vietnamese]

11:03.966 --> 11:05.865
♪ mnh mnh ♪

11:05.901 --> 11:10.036
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh, mnh-mnh ♪

11:10.072 --> 11:11.938
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh ♪

11:11.974 --> 11:14.074
♪ mnh, mnh, mnh-mnh ♪

11:20.115 --> 11:22.682
[horns honking in distance]

11:25.721 --> 11:30.090
[vehicle approaching,
tires screech in distance]

11:54.716 --> 11:57.751
[window motor whirs]

11:57.786 --> 12:00.320
Hey! It's me!

12:00.355 --> 12:01.454
[brake squeaks]

12:02.057 --> 12:05.058
Geez. Hello?

12:05.060 --> 12:07.026
Hello?

12:08.931 --> 12:11.432
It's me. I got a new car.

12:11.464 --> 12:13.380
You like it?

12:13.433 --> 12:15.883
We're not taking that to the meet.

12:15.935 --> 12:18.135
How are we gonna get there?

12:19.856 --> 12:21.772
I'll drive.

12:21.808 --> 12:22.973
My car.

12:22.975 --> 12:24.141
Why?

12:24.193 --> 12:27.111
This business requires restraint.

12:27.146 --> 12:30.898
That is the opposite of restraint.

12:30.950 --> 12:33.317
But... I like it.

12:33.369 --> 12:34.652
I mean, I'm proud of it.

12:34.704 --> 12:36.320
Good.

12:36.322 --> 12:38.456
Then you be proud of it on your
own time, but not with me.

12:38.491 --> 12:40.157
I'm not getting in that.

12:42.795 --> 12:46.163
Okay. Then... then don't.

12:46.215 --> 12:50.000
Honestly, uh, you don't really do anything.

12:50.052 --> 12:53.003
I've been paying you
the salary of three people

12:53.005 --> 12:55.422
to just stand behind me.

12:55.475 --> 12:57.341
You know? And... And these...
these last few deals...

12:57.393 --> 12:59.927
This Nacho fella, he's been coming alone.

12:59.979 --> 13:01.679
I mean, if he doesn't need backup men,

13:01.731 --> 13:05.015
then, I mean, why do I need you?

13:05.067 --> 13:06.484
I should just go alone.

13:06.519 --> 13:08.519
I'm throwing... I'm throwing away money.

13:08.521 --> 13:10.521
Just tossing it away.

13:10.573 --> 13:12.690
Into the trash.

13:12.692 --> 13:14.825
Look, you do whatever you want,

13:14.861 --> 13:17.278
but I'm advising you...
do not go to that meet

13:17.330 --> 13:19.163
without someone watching your back.

13:19.198 --> 13:21.115
Yeah, well, of course you're gonna say that.

13:21.167 --> 13:24.618
I mean, you don't want to be
out of this easy-peasy job.

13:24.670 --> 13:27.838
Well, I'm sorry,
but this is the gravy train,

13:27.874 --> 13:30.374
and it's leaving the station right now.

13:30.409 --> 13:34.378
So last chance.

13:34.413 --> 13:36.280
All aboard.

13:39.685 --> 13:41.218
Seriously, last chance.

13:41.254 --> 13:45.523
I'm gonna count to, say, 10, and then I'm...

13:45.558 --> 13:47.474
All right, then.

13:47.527 --> 13:49.760
Your services are no longer needed!

13:52.231 --> 13:54.732
[Bird cawing]

14:25.898 --> 14:27.965
[Engine shuts off]

14:33.940 --> 14:35.239
<i>Hola.</i>

14:38.578 --> 14:39.827
No old guy?

14:39.862 --> 14:42.246
What, did he break a hip or something?

14:42.281 --> 14:43.747
[Chuckles] I know, right?

14:43.783 --> 14:45.449
Yeah, no, we, uh...

14:45.451 --> 14:47.284
We... we parted ways.

14:47.336 --> 14:49.119
Yeah, saw things differently.

14:49.121 --> 14:51.839
So... You know how it is.

15:04.303 --> 15:06.303
This is interesting.

15:06.355 --> 15:08.606
Oh, yeah. You like it?

15:08.641 --> 15:10.808
Can I take a look?

15:10.810 --> 15:12.643
Oh. Be my guest. Get in.

15:12.645 --> 15:14.528
[Chuckles] Check it out.

15:17.149 --> 15:18.482
Wow.

15:24.156 --> 15:25.656
Impressive.

15:25.691 --> 15:27.708
Thank you. Get in. Feel the leather.

15:28.995 --> 15:31.662
Yeah, it's a H2.

15:31.714 --> 15:33.130
Brand-new off the line.

15:33.165 --> 15:36.500
Slimmer than the H1 but longer, more height.

15:36.502 --> 15:38.002
Yeah, it's a honey.

15:38.054 --> 15:43.173
V-8 engine, 325 horsepower,
tri-zone climate controls.

15:43.175 --> 15:46.927
So you can have a girl in
a bikini and another in a parka,

15:46.979 --> 15:49.513
and they're both gonna
be comfortable. [Chuckles]

15:49.515 --> 15:51.849
You're running around
with two girls in your S.U.V.,

15:51.901 --> 15:53.651
you'd be really comfortable, huh?

15:53.686 --> 15:54.935
Oh, yeah. Yes.

15:54.987 --> 15:56.153
[Chuckles]

15:56.188 --> 15:57.488
I'm gonna count this quick.

15:57.523 --> 16:00.858
Do your thing. Make sure it's right.

16:12.922 --> 16:14.705
Okeydokey.

16:14.707 --> 16:17.875
We are good.

16:17.877 --> 16:20.544
Uh, same as before.

16:20.596 --> 16:22.746
Uh, still factory-sealed.

16:22.782 --> 16:25.849
And, as always, you're
welcome to count them.

16:25.885 --> 16:26.884
I trust you.

16:26.886 --> 16:29.386
Great. Thank you.

16:31.273 --> 16:33.223
See you next time.

16:33.275 --> 16:34.775
[Door closes]

17:07.191 --> 17:10.026
[Cellphone ringing]

17:17.858 --> 17:19.358
[Cellphone beeps]

17:19.411 --> 17:20.660
Hello?

17:20.694 --> 17:22.862
Yes.

17:22.914 --> 17:24.946
Uh, no. Sorry.

17:25.000 --> 17:27.165
But... Yes, this is James McGill,

17:27.202 --> 17:30.036
but I'm no longer a lawyer, so...

17:30.088 --> 17:32.372
That's right... not a lawyer. Bye.

17:32.424 --> 17:34.907
[Cellphone beeps]

17:34.943 --> 17:37.210
[Sighs]

17:37.262 --> 17:39.679
So, this is what
a midlife crisis looks like?

17:39.714 --> 17:42.215
Not midlife crisis.

17:42.267 --> 17:43.716
Clarity.

17:43.718 --> 17:45.018
Midlife clarity.

17:45.053 --> 17:47.020
Clarity? Huh.

17:47.055 --> 17:48.938
Clearly explain to me why you walked out

17:48.973 --> 17:51.391
on the best job opportunity of your life.

17:51.443 --> 17:53.359
[Sighs]

17:53.395 --> 17:55.895
Get in the pool, and I'll tell ya.

17:55.897 --> 17:57.447
Get in the pool?

17:57.482 --> 17:59.916
[Chuckling] Yeah. Come on.

17:59.939 --> 18:01.906
Just pop in the gift shop
and buy a bathing suit...

18:01.941 --> 18:03.407
get a one-piece, nothing fancy.

18:03.443 --> 18:05.860
The water is perfect. It's 82 degrees.

18:05.862 --> 18:07.278
You can order a drink.

18:07.330 --> 18:08.746
And you got to try this crab dip.

18:08.781 --> 18:10.198
Why are you acting like this?

18:10.200 --> 18:12.083
I'm not acting like anything.

18:12.118 --> 18:16.438
I just... finally decided to be me.

18:16.447 --> 18:19.164
Everything okay, Mr. Cumpston?
Would you like another drink?

18:19.200 --> 18:21.950
Uh, I'm good with this.

18:24.505 --> 18:27.122
I'll tell you what, Mr. Cumpston.

18:27.174 --> 18:29.458
If you really want to talk,
I'll be in the bar.

18:29.460 --> 18:31.343
Not for long.

18:36.016 --> 18:37.299
Hey, Rolando.

18:37.301 --> 18:40.102
Check.

18:40.137 --> 18:44.356
What do... What do you mean "quit the law"?

18:44.391 --> 18:46.642
- [ <i> "Buena Vista"</i> plays in background]
- I quit it. Simple as that.

18:46.644 --> 18:49.194
Oh, well, thanks for explaining, Jimmy.

18:49.230 --> 18:51.280
- It's super-clear now.
- Hey, buddy?

18:51.315 --> 18:53.198
Uh, is that a misprint right there?

18:53.234 --> 18:54.316
It's got to be, right?

18:54.318 --> 18:55.701
- The Zafiro Anejo?
- Yeah.

18:55.736 --> 18:57.453
That's correct, actually, believe it or not.

18:57.488 --> 19:00.322
Holy shit. A $50 shot of tequila?

19:00.324 --> 19:02.541
Is it worth it? Apparently.

19:02.576 --> 19:04.193
I mean, it's kind of a
personal-choice kind of thing.

19:04.228 --> 19:07.713
Well, I can't die without trying
a $50 shot of tequila,

19:07.748 --> 19:10.466
so, uh... two... <i>dos</i>... neat.

19:10.501 --> 19:12.334
And, uh, we can charge that
to the room, can't we?

19:12.386 --> 19:15.888
No, we can't. We...

19:15.923 --> 19:17.556
I am paying.

19:17.591 --> 19:20.175
And he will be having a shot
of your well brand,

19:20.177 --> 19:22.060
and I'll have a glass of your house red.

19:22.096 --> 19:25.347
We have a Cabernet, a Pinot, and a Syrah.

19:25.399 --> 19:27.683
Whatever. Dealer's choice.

19:27.735 --> 19:29.067
Something with alcohol.

19:29.103 --> 19:30.853
You got it.

19:30.855 --> 19:33.021
[Sighs]

19:35.025 --> 19:38.694
Jimmy... did something happen in Cicero?

19:38.696 --> 19:40.863
Why did something have to happen in Cicero?

19:40.915 --> 19:42.998
Because when I talked to you
about Davis & Main,

19:43.033 --> 19:44.533
you were ready to take the job.

19:44.535 --> 19:46.869
Now you're back, and you're
suddenly quitting the law,

19:46.921 --> 19:49.037
cheating hotels out of expensive liquor,

19:49.039 --> 19:51.590
wearing a weird pinkie ring?

19:51.625 --> 19:53.709
What, are you in the Mafia now?

19:55.546 --> 19:58.881
Asking if we have a future.

19:58.933 --> 20:02.518
I mean, where did that come from?

20:02.553 --> 20:06.054
I don't know. I just...

20:06.106 --> 20:08.557
Well, Cicero has nothing to do with it.

20:08.559 --> 20:10.192
It's my whole life.

20:10.227 --> 20:14.563
Well, my life since Chuck
made me come to Albuquerque.

20:14.615 --> 20:16.031
Ever since I got here,

20:16.066 --> 20:18.567
all I've done is try to make Chuck happy,

20:18.619 --> 20:21.236
bend over backwards to please Chuck.

20:21.288 --> 20:24.573
Chuck, Chuck, Chuck. Well, no more.

20:24.575 --> 20:27.960
You quitting the law... isn't
that exactly what Chuck wants?

20:27.995 --> 20:29.211
Who cares?

20:29.246 --> 20:31.463
This is for me, okay?

20:31.498 --> 20:34.216
I-I got into the law
for all the wrong reasons.

20:34.251 --> 20:36.134
I'm trusting my instincts.

20:36.170 --> 20:39.304
I think that my talents
are better spent elsewhere.

20:39.340 --> 20:42.090
Where? Floating in somebody else's pool?

20:42.092 --> 20:44.426
- [Scoffs]
- [Sighs]

20:44.428 --> 20:46.645
Jimmy, you're a great lawyer.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.263
Why give that up?

20:48.315 --> 20:50.599
I'm not saying it didn't have its moments,

20:50.601 --> 20:52.317
but the stuff I liked about it...

20:52.353 --> 20:54.269
selling people, convincing people...

20:54.271 --> 20:56.305
I don't have to be a lawyer to do that.

20:56.340 --> 20:59.658
Besides, people tell me how they see me,

20:59.693 --> 21:01.276
and it's not as a lawyer.

21:01.278 --> 21:04.112
All right. Here you go.

21:04.164 --> 21:05.781
Thank you.

21:05.783 --> 21:07.833
Lemme know if I can get
you guys anything else, okay?

21:07.868 --> 21:09.785
KEN: Bobby, what up, brother man?

21:09.787 --> 21:10.953
Oh, thanks.

21:11.005 --> 21:13.589
Short it.

21:13.624 --> 21:14.840
Short it.

21:14.875 --> 21:17.626
Short it. Short that shit.

21:17.628 --> 21:19.511
That stock is useless. It's got no legs.

21:19.546 --> 21:21.346
It's like a circus freak minus the fun.

21:21.382 --> 21:22.881
And that one's even worse.
Who's giving you these?

21:22.933 --> 21:24.433
Please do me a favor.

21:24.468 --> 21:26.802
Take a pillow, put it over that stock's face

21:26.854 --> 21:28.553
until you hear the deathbed queef.

21:28.606 --> 21:30.639
- KEN: It's a loser.
- Okay, so...

21:30.641 --> 21:32.307
if you're not gonna be a lawyer, then what?

21:32.359 --> 21:36.311
Float around and wait for your
Sandpiper money to roll in?

21:36.363 --> 21:38.196
No. That could take years.

21:38.232 --> 21:40.399
Sandpiper has no bearing on this at all.

21:40.451 --> 21:42.034
<i>Yeah, it's got legs.</i>

21:42.069 --> 21:44.369
Okay, then, what's the plan?

21:44.405 --> 21:46.321
To be open to the universe.

21:46.373 --> 21:48.206
Okay, so no plan.

21:48.242 --> 21:50.959
Just walk the Earth, like Jules
at the end of "Pulp Fiction"?

21:51.011 --> 21:53.512
Look, whatever the universe presents,

21:53.547 --> 21:56.598
whatever opportunity arises, I will take it.

21:56.634 --> 21:58.133
- Whatever opportunity?
- Yeah.

21:58.135 --> 22:00.636
Wasn't Davis & Main an opportunity?

22:00.638 --> 22:03.105
It's a great opportunity,
and you're walking away from it.

22:03.140 --> 22:04.640
Not him, not the guy who...

22:04.642 --> 22:09.528
Look, shouldn't you at least try
the job before you say no?

22:09.563 --> 22:11.647
And waste everyone's time, including my own?

22:11.699 --> 22:14.316
Kim, I appreciate your concern,
but it's not for me.

22:14.368 --> 22:15.901
I don't want it.

22:15.953 --> 22:19.154
Jimmy, do you remember how long
you studied for that bar?

22:19.206 --> 22:20.989
How hard you worked?

22:20.991 --> 22:23.875
All that effort, you're
just gonna toss it away?

22:23.911 --> 22:25.994
That's the Sunk Cost Fallacy.

22:25.996 --> 22:27.462
W... The what?

22:27.498 --> 22:30.716
The Fallacy of Sunk Cost...
It's what gamblers do.

22:30.751 --> 22:32.501
They throw good money after bad

22:32.553 --> 22:34.169
thinking they can turn their luck around.

22:34.221 --> 22:37.172
It's like, "I've already spent
this much money or time...

22:37.174 --> 22:39.307
whatever. I got to keep going!"

22:39.343 --> 22:41.677
No, there's no reward
at the end of this game.

22:41.679 --> 22:44.229
You are making a mistake.

22:44.264 --> 22:46.014
I know you're making a mistake.

22:46.066 --> 22:48.350
I've been doing the "right"
thing for all these years now,

22:48.352 --> 22:50.185
and where has it gotten me? Nowhere.

22:50.237 --> 22:51.820
I'm sorry. I don't...

22:51.855 --> 22:53.572
[Sighs]

22:53.607 --> 22:55.691
[ <i> "Transatlantic"</i> plays in background]

22:55.693 --> 22:57.492
<i>It's not my thing.</i>

22:57.528 --> 22:59.027
I don't get it.

22:59.029 --> 23:01.363
- I just don't get it.
- It's what's right for me.

23:01.365 --> 23:02.497
<i>[Laughs]</i>

23:02.533 --> 23:04.499
<i>Donkey balls.</i>

23:04.535 --> 23:05.701
<i>Pure donkey balls, dude.</i>

23:05.703 --> 23:07.002
<i>Wall Street's for suckers.</i>

23:07.037 --> 23:09.004
<i>Who needs that aggravation?</i>

23:09.039 --> 23:11.089
<i>If the the Oracle doesn't have to live
there, then I sure as hell don't.</i>

23:11.125 --> 23:13.875
<i>I can make a million-dollar
stock trade on my laptop</i>

23:13.927 --> 23:15.377
<i>sitting on a toilet.</i>

23:15.379 --> 23:17.679
<i>Like Midas, shitting gold bricks
on my throne.</i>

23:17.715 --> 23:20.048
<i>That's why Speigelman and Deitch
want my business so bad.</i>

23:20.100 --> 23:22.050
<i>I'm a golden God.</i>

23:22.052 --> 23:24.553
<i>Look, of course I remember that.
Who forgets a thing like that?</i>

23:24.605 --> 23:27.222
<i>That fart had the anger of
a repressed minority community.</i>

23:27.274 --> 23:28.557
<i>You fart like that in someone's face,</i>

23:28.609 --> 23:30.025
<i>you're gonna give them pinkeye for life.</i>

23:30.060 --> 23:31.727
<i>[Laughs]</i>

23:31.779 --> 23:33.445
<i>Good convo, bro.</i>

23:33.480 --> 23:35.397
<i>Till next time, brutha-man.</i>

23:35.449 --> 23:37.232
<i>- Flip side. On it.</i>
- Come with me.

23:37.234 --> 23:40.068
- What?
- Just come on. Trust me.

23:40.070 --> 23:41.903
What are you gonna do?

23:41.955 --> 23:43.989
You want to understand
what I'm talking about?

23:44.041 --> 23:45.574
Follow my lead.

23:47.995 --> 23:50.245
[Indistinct conversations]

23:54.802 --> 23:58.170
Hey, buddy, could you settle a bet for us?

23:58.222 --> 23:59.838
- I what?
- Uh, sorry.

23:59.890 --> 24:01.590
I don't want to make it sound
like I was eavesdropping,

24:01.642 --> 24:03.175
but I kind of was.

24:03.227 --> 24:05.527
Uh, we heard you talking about stocks.

24:05.562 --> 24:07.562
Uh-huh.

24:07.598 --> 24:09.181
Yeah, so, question...

24:09.233 --> 24:12.601
if you could settle a debate
between me and my sister.

24:12.603 --> 24:14.686
Uh, you know what?
We probably shouldn't be bothering this...

24:14.738 --> 24:16.104
We wouldn't normally do this... Right?

24:16.106 --> 24:17.522
but we need an expert.

24:17.574 --> 24:19.407
This guy sounds like he knows his stuff.

24:20.944 --> 24:22.911
Yeah, go.

24:22.946 --> 24:24.446
Okay. Here's the question.

24:24.448 --> 24:26.581
Uh, when it comes to the stock market,

24:26.617 --> 24:28.366
is there, like, a financial limit

24:28.418 --> 24:31.703
to how much a person's allowed to invest?

24:31.755 --> 24:34.005
A limit?

24:34.041 --> 24:36.124
No. No limit.

24:36.126 --> 24:38.960
Knew it. Oh, even if it's an inheritance?

24:38.962 --> 24:41.296
You know, with, like,
inheritance taxes and whatnot?

24:41.298 --> 24:42.631
Nope. Same.

24:42.633 --> 24:44.716
That's... Oh, fantastic. Thank you, buddy.

24:44.768 --> 24:48.270
See? No limit. Told you
we could invest it all.

24:48.305 --> 24:50.021
And it's a smart move, too.

24:50.057 --> 24:51.473
Sticking it <i> all</i> in the bank? No.

24:51.475 --> 24:55.227
Um, yeah. You can... invest all your money.

24:55.279 --> 24:56.862
Just make sure you diversify.

24:56.897 --> 24:59.064
Yeah. Diversify.

24:59.116 --> 25:01.533
[Clicks tongue] That's... You got to...

25:01.568 --> 25:02.651
Oh, hey, um...

25:02.653 --> 25:04.536
What do you mean, "diversify"?

25:04.571 --> 25:06.454
Well, diversify is...

25:06.490 --> 25:07.906
Y-You know that saying,

25:07.958 --> 25:10.125
"Don't put all your eggs
in one basket," right?

25:10.160 --> 25:11.543
Same principle.

25:11.578 --> 25:13.378
No, it makes complete sense. Thank you.

25:13.413 --> 25:14.963
Now, if I had an idea of the
money we're talking about...

25:14.998 --> 25:17.048
Ballpark... I could give you examples

25:17.084 --> 25:19.167
of smart diversification.

25:19.169 --> 25:22.804
[Sighs] Yeah, um...

25:22.840 --> 25:26.057
Look, an uncle on our father's
side recently passed,

25:26.093 --> 25:32.347
and he left us somewhere in the
neighborhood of $1.4 million.

25:32.349 --> 25:34.933
And I don't mean to be greedy, but I think,

25:34.985 --> 25:38.270
if we invest it smart now,
we could double it, triple it...

25:38.322 --> 25:41.823
we could quadruple
the whole inheritance, right?

25:41.859 --> 25:43.942
In my opinion?

25:43.994 --> 25:45.911
Fortune favors the bold, man.

25:45.946 --> 25:48.113
Now, if you guys are free
to join me for a drink,

25:48.165 --> 25:49.414
I can give you a quick consult.

25:49.449 --> 25:51.199
That's all right.
We were gonna do it ourselves

25:51.251 --> 25:53.034
through one of those online
brokerage websites.

25:53.086 --> 25:55.954
We're just gonna pick,
uh, a classic, like...

25:56.006 --> 25:57.756
I think they're called blue-chip stocks?

25:57.791 --> 25:59.674
Yeah, yeah, yeah, you can
totally do it yourself.

25:59.710 --> 26:01.459
Shoot for the tried and true.

26:01.511 --> 26:03.178
'Course, you might be putting
your cash in the Hindenburg,

26:03.213 --> 26:06.264
the Andrea Doria, uh..."Corky Romano."

26:06.300 --> 26:07.766
- [Chuckles]
- Right?

26:07.801 --> 26:10.552
They all seemed rock-solid
beforehand, but then...

26:10.604 --> 26:12.137
Yeah, not good.

26:12.189 --> 26:13.471
Not good, yeah.

26:13.523 --> 26:15.056
So, how do you know?

26:15.058 --> 26:18.360
Well, that's where someone
like myself comes in.

26:18.395 --> 26:19.728
Proven track record as a wealth manager.

26:19.730 --> 26:22.530
I take calculated but aggressive risks

26:22.566 --> 26:24.532
'cause I want to catch lightning.

26:24.568 --> 26:25.901
And I do.

26:25.903 --> 26:27.319
Practically a money-printing machine.

26:27.371 --> 26:28.536
[Chuckling] That sounds good.

26:28.572 --> 26:31.623
A money-printing machine.

26:31.658 --> 26:34.326
Listen, there's a little booth over here.

26:34.378 --> 26:37.162
There's some privacy.
We can talk. No obligations.

26:37.214 --> 26:39.414
We can just... just rap
about this a little bit.

26:39.416 --> 26:41.750
- Yeah, I guess.
- Yeah?

26:41.752 --> 26:44.002
What do you say, sis?

26:44.054 --> 26:46.554
Can we just talk?

26:48.842 --> 26:50.675
Electric slide on in there.

26:50.727 --> 26:52.260
And we'll just rap a little bit. It's no...

26:52.262 --> 26:54.012
My name's Ken, by the way.

26:54.064 --> 26:55.764
Uh, Viktor, with a "K."

26:55.766 --> 26:57.682
Cool. Viktor with a "K."

26:57.734 --> 27:00.769
And this lovely lady is?

27:02.572 --> 27:06.241
It's... Giselle. Giselle Saint Claire.

27:06.276 --> 27:07.492
Ah, lovely.

27:07.527 --> 27:13.281
Please, sit. I won't bite.

27:13.283 --> 27:17.252
So, Viktor with a "K"
and Giselle... exotic names.

27:17.287 --> 27:18.536
JIMMY: They're Dutch.

27:18.588 --> 27:20.672
Well, Boer, to be precise.

27:20.707 --> 27:23.458
Our... father's side of the
family is from South Africa,

27:23.460 --> 27:26.428
which is where uncle Humphrey passed away.

27:26.463 --> 27:27.796
South Africa.

27:27.798 --> 27:29.431
They grow them beautiful down there, right?

27:29.466 --> 27:31.599
Charlize Theron. And you.

27:31.635 --> 27:34.352
Oh. Well...

27:34.388 --> 27:37.105
I've never actually been,
but hope to go someday.

27:37.140 --> 27:38.707
Tell you what, by the time
I'm done with you two,

27:38.742 --> 27:40.709
you might be taking your own private jet.

27:40.744 --> 27:42.143
Nice.

27:42.145 --> 27:44.396
Excuse me. Hi. Uh, we are sitting here now,

27:44.448 --> 27:46.731
so, uh, we could use a wine
list, if you get a chance...

27:46.783 --> 27:48.550
Hey, uh, are a tequila fan?

27:48.585 --> 27:50.318
Yes.

27:50.354 --> 27:51.569
You down for that?

27:51.621 --> 27:54.990
You ever try Zafiro Anejo?

27:54.992 --> 27:56.958
No, I have not, but I'm down for whatever.

27:56.994 --> 27:58.493
Three of whatever she just said.

27:58.495 --> 28:00.879
- You got it.
- All right.

28:00.914 --> 28:03.331
So, stock market. A great investment.

28:03.333 --> 28:05.500
And you're picking
the right time to jump in.

28:05.535 --> 28:07.135
- [ <i> "Goldigger"</i> plays in background]
- Why do you listen to me? I'm an idiot.

28:07.170 --> 28:08.470
[Laughs]

28:08.505 --> 28:10.839
And talks about his cars, talks about...

28:10.841 --> 28:12.474
[Jimmy and Ken laugh]

28:12.509 --> 28:13.892
- How many cars did he have?
- I don't think...

28:13.927 --> 28:17.062
[Laughter]

28:17.097 --> 28:19.647
- It doesn't make sense.
- That's it, Ken.

28:19.683 --> 28:20.932
Oh, yeah.

28:20.984 --> 28:22.317
Compliments of the bartender.

28:22.352 --> 28:23.685
She thought you might want a souvenir.

28:23.687 --> 28:25.820
Oh, my God. Did we drink the entire bottle?

28:25.856 --> 28:26.988
Not yet, we didn't.

28:27.024 --> 28:28.490
- Boom.
- Hey, hey, cheers.

28:28.525 --> 28:30.859
Uh, I think we're ready for the check.

28:32.279 --> 28:34.863
[Laughter]

28:34.865 --> 28:36.614
[Groans]

28:36.666 --> 28:39.751
No, really, it's the smart way to go.

28:39.786 --> 28:42.120
KIM: Okay. But, so, to be clear,

28:42.172 --> 28:45.540
you take the money directly
from our account and invest it.

28:45.542 --> 28:47.876
- Diversify.
- Diversify it.

28:47.878 --> 28:50.595
And then all the dividends
and all the profits

28:50.630 --> 28:53.298
and the...what-have-you
comes back into our account.

28:53.350 --> 28:55.600
Boom. Absolutely.

28:55.635 --> 28:56.935
And you'll get a detailed statement

28:56.970 --> 28:58.686
showing you how much
your money is growing...

28:58.722 --> 29:00.438
biggest bulls of the month, et cetera.

29:00.474 --> 29:04.309
Ken, buddy... let's do this.

29:05.729 --> 29:07.946
Great. Right there, Viktor with a "K,"

29:07.981 --> 29:09.397
and, Giselle, you are next.

29:09.399 --> 29:11.032
- This is so exciting.
- Mm-hmm.

29:11.068 --> 29:12.534
Folks, it's been a pleasure.

29:12.569 --> 29:13.952
- Oops, I got that.
- Can't let you do it, son.

29:13.987 --> 29:16.988
Wait. What? Ken, you are the greatest.

29:17.040 --> 29:18.490
- Thank you.
- No problem-o.

29:18.542 --> 29:19.874
Hey, this will be the best
decision you'll ever make.

29:19.910 --> 29:21.376
Oh, I believe it.

29:21.411 --> 29:22.911
All right, well,
we should get out of your hair.

29:22.913 --> 29:24.412
- Yeah.
- Oh, wait, wait.

29:24.414 --> 29:27.048
This... is for you.

29:27.084 --> 29:28.583
Now, that's got all my contact info.

29:28.585 --> 29:32.470
Call me anytime with questions
or anything at all.

29:32.506 --> 29:33.805
Ken.

29:33.840 --> 29:35.974
Bye. Call me, guys.

29:36.009 --> 29:37.642
- Bye.
- Try and stop us.

29:37.677 --> 29:39.427
[Laughs]

29:39.429 --> 29:41.930
Wow.

29:41.982 --> 29:43.398
[Chuckles]

29:43.433 --> 29:46.768
Just wow.

29:46.770 --> 29:49.104
[Inhales deeply]

29:49.156 --> 29:50.605
[Chuckles]

29:55.495 --> 29:58.947
[Exhales slowly]

29:58.949 --> 30:01.816
Hey.

30:01.852 --> 30:03.785
What I...

30:03.837 --> 30:05.420
Is this right?

30:05.455 --> 30:07.956
Yes, sir, it is.

30:12.129 --> 30:13.344
- [ <i>"Music & Wine"</i> plays in background]
- KIM: Go, go, go, go, go!

30:13.380 --> 30:15.597
[Both laugh]

30:15.632 --> 30:17.966
- Zafiro Anejo!
- Shh!

30:17.968 --> 30:20.135
He's gonna come out. [Laughs]

30:20.137 --> 30:21.636
Oh, no.

30:21.638 --> 30:23.138
I didn't read the fine print.

30:23.140 --> 30:25.473
- Wait.
- Yeah!

30:25.525 --> 30:27.392
[Both laugh]

30:27.444 --> 30:28.810
Holy crap.

30:28.862 --> 30:30.311
I can't b...

30:30.363 --> 30:33.531
[Laughing]

30:33.567 --> 30:37.318
[Breathes deeply]

30:37.320 --> 30:39.487
[Chuckles]

30:39.539 --> 30:42.157
[Chuckles]

30:42.159 --> 30:45.243
[Laughter, indistinct conversations]

30:58.779 --> 31:00.497
[Water turns on]

31:12.628 --> 31:15.295
Can I borrow that when you're done?

31:15.297 --> 31:17.797
[Chuckles] No, that's gross.

31:17.849 --> 31:19.549
H-how is it gross?

31:19.601 --> 31:21.301
Our germs have already intermingled.

31:21.303 --> 31:24.387
It's my toothbrush. It's different.

31:24.439 --> 31:25.889
Why is it different?

31:25.941 --> 31:27.807
Because.

31:27.859 --> 31:30.026
You know, gums bleed, and there's...

31:30.062 --> 31:34.197
there's cold sores,
all sorts of food and weir...

31:34.232 --> 31:35.231
Let me see that. Come on.

31:35.284 --> 31:36.483
What? No!

31:36.518 --> 31:37.867
Come on! I'll do it right now.

31:37.903 --> 31:39.319
- I don't care.
- I need to brush my teeth.

31:39.371 --> 31:40.870
I don't have an extra. It's not my problem.

31:40.906 --> 31:43.823
That's fine. I got this.

31:48.380 --> 31:49.829
Good. I'm fine with this.

31:49.881 --> 31:51.414
Yeah, me too.

31:51.466 --> 31:52.916
Wait till you see what I floss with.

31:52.968 --> 31:55.468
[Laughing]

32:05.931 --> 32:08.014
[Jewelry clattering]

32:13.855 --> 32:16.239
That's a keeper.

32:16.274 --> 32:19.743
[Chuckles] Thank you, Viktor with a "K."

32:22.164 --> 32:25.198
Hey, wouldn't it be great
if we could do that every night?

32:25.250 --> 32:27.283
Yes, it would.

32:29.921 --> 32:31.921
But...

32:31.957 --> 32:34.958
We can't.

32:35.010 --> 32:37.043
I know, yeah.

32:37.045 --> 32:41.297
But I'm just saying,
if we could, it would be great.

32:41.350 --> 32:43.466
But I know we can't.

32:43.518 --> 32:46.886
Oh, crap. I can't be late today.

32:47.689 --> 32:49.556
Howard is doling out assignments,

32:49.558 --> 32:51.441
and the last one through the door

32:51.476 --> 32:54.728
could get stuck in doc review.

32:58.749 --> 33:00.549
You got somewhere to go?

33:00.585 --> 33:04.536
Yeah. Uh, yeah, I got somewhere.

33:12.380 --> 33:14.179
You good?

33:14.215 --> 33:17.349
[Sighs] Yeah. All good.

33:19.996 --> 33:21.079
[Door closes]

33:21.131 --> 33:23.164
[Dog barks in distance]

33:25.969 --> 33:29.053
[Brakes squeak]

33:29.089 --> 33:31.589
[Engine shuts off]

33:32.842 --> 33:35.343
[Police radio chatter]

33:44.854 --> 33:47.822
[Barking continues]

33:47.857 --> 33:49.741
[Knock on door]

33:51.635 --> 33:52.718
Daniel Wormald?

33:52.754 --> 33:54.537
I'm Officer Baker. This is Officer Saxton.

33:54.589 --> 33:57.623
Yeah, please. Come on in.

33:57.676 --> 34:00.710
Come in. It's over here.

34:00.762 --> 34:02.462
See what they did?

34:02.514 --> 34:03.796
I mean, all gone.

34:03.848 --> 34:05.181
All of them, just...

34:05.216 --> 34:06.849
Uh, what's all gone?

34:06.885 --> 34:09.936
I have... I <i> had</i>
a baseball-card collection...

34:09.971 --> 34:12.304
a <i>major</i> collection... All stolen.

34:12.357 --> 34:14.107
Oh, sorry to hear that.

34:14.141 --> 34:16.391
Uh, was it common knowledge
that you have baseball cards?

34:16.444 --> 34:18.277
No, not really.

34:18.313 --> 34:20.980
So, nobody in particular
you can think of wanting them?

34:21.032 --> 34:23.983
No. Not that I... No.

34:24.034 --> 34:25.451
How'd they get in?

34:25.487 --> 34:28.321
Uh, the back door over here.

34:28.373 --> 34:30.123
It was open when I came home for lunch.

34:30.158 --> 34:31.708
I mean, it was locked,

34:31.743 --> 34:34.460
but they must have jimmied it
open or something.

34:34.496 --> 34:35.795
Uh-huh.

34:35.830 --> 34:38.380
At what time, uh, you figure this happened?

34:38.416 --> 34:41.551
I left for work at 8:15,
came home for lunch at 12:30,

34:41.585 --> 34:42.719
and called you immediately.

34:42.754 --> 34:44.170
Was anything else taken?

34:44.222 --> 34:46.556
Cash... a fair bit. Uh, um...

34:46.591 --> 34:47.924
How much cash?

34:47.976 --> 34:49.509
Uh, I don't know.

34:49.561 --> 34:52.645
You know, let's focus on
what's important here, you know?

34:52.679 --> 34:55.098
All I really care about
are my baseball cards.

34:55.150 --> 34:57.767
You know, I have a Topps
Mickey Mantle rookie card

34:57.819 --> 34:59.435
that's irreplaceable.

34:59.487 --> 35:02.488
It's a mint, 60/40, 90/10 on the reverse.

35:02.524 --> 35:03.656
I can go on.

35:03.691 --> 35:05.358
All my cards are in top-loaders,

35:05.410 --> 35:08.161
but if they're taken out
and exposed to the elements,

35:08.196 --> 35:10.913
I mean, or creased, God forbid,

35:10.949 --> 35:12.482
I mean, you're looking at
a 9-point downgrade

35:12.517 --> 35:14.717
in a matter of seconds.

35:14.753 --> 35:16.536
I understand the first 48 hours

35:16.588 --> 35:19.288
are the most important
in investigations like this,

35:19.340 --> 35:21.007
so the more time passes,

35:21.042 --> 35:23.876
I mean, the less likely
we are of a recovery.

35:23.928 --> 35:28.431
So...time is of the essence here, guys.

35:28.466 --> 35:30.933
Well, we're gonna help you out
the best we can, Mr. Wormald.

35:30.969 --> 35:32.552
Good.

35:32.604 --> 35:35.438
Well...they really tossed this place.

35:35.473 --> 35:36.856
-[Scoffs]
-I mean, are you sure

35:36.891 --> 35:38.891
they weren't looking for anything else?

35:38.943 --> 35:40.476
Like what?

35:40.478 --> 35:43.446
I don't know.
J-Just wondering your thoughts.

35:43.481 --> 35:46.282
I assume more baseball cards.

35:46.317 --> 35:48.918
Did you have more baseball cards than the
ones you keep locked in that case here?

35:48.953 --> 35:50.987
Yes, in... in back... thousands.

35:50.989 --> 35:53.906
But these were the crown jewels over here.

35:53.958 --> 35:55.908
You know, t-the all-star lineup.

35:55.960 --> 35:58.494
Right.

35:58.496 --> 35:59.962
Hmm.

35:59.998 --> 36:02.999
What?

36:03.001 --> 36:04.550
Just trying to make sense of it.

36:04.586 --> 36:06.636
What's to make sense of?
I mean, isn't it as simple

36:06.671 --> 36:09.472
as the perp was looking
for more baseball cards?

36:09.507 --> 36:11.307
Or hopped up on speed or whatever

36:11.342 --> 36:14.060
and went nuts with the vandalism?

36:14.095 --> 36:16.262
Yeah. I mean, that could be.

36:16.314 --> 36:18.598
Yeah.

36:18.650 --> 36:20.266
Pretty sweet Hummer parked in the driveway.

36:20.318 --> 36:21.684
That yours?

36:21.719 --> 36:22.852
Yeah, that's mine.

36:22.854 --> 36:25.188
Uh, it's a lease.

36:25.190 --> 36:28.407
Got a great deal on it.

36:28.443 --> 36:31.494
It's very sweet.

36:31.529 --> 36:33.196
You know, they say Arnold Schwarzenegger

36:33.198 --> 36:34.697
is the reason that Hummers exist.

36:34.699 --> 36:36.999
I don't know how, but that's what they say.

36:37.035 --> 36:37.667
- No kidding.
- Yeah.

36:37.702 --> 36:39.752
Huh.

36:39.787 --> 36:42.588
What kind of work do you do, Mr. Wormald?

36:42.624 --> 36:44.423
Uh, I work I.T.,

36:44.459 --> 36:47.627
uh, for a pharmaceutical company.

36:47.679 --> 36:49.679
Wow. Computers.

36:49.714 --> 36:52.014
God, I should've gotten into computers.

36:52.050 --> 36:54.350
- I'd have that same Hummer.
- [Chuckles] Yeah, right.

36:54.385 --> 36:56.719
Look, guys, I'm glad you like my car,

36:56.721 --> 36:58.471
but I think we're looking through

36:58.523 --> 37:01.057
the wrong end of the telescope here.

37:01.059 --> 37:03.943
You know, the priority is my baseball cards.

37:03.978 --> 37:05.194
Of course.

37:05.230 --> 37:07.563
Yes, now, I have a detailed manifest

37:07.615 --> 37:09.866
of my entire collection

37:09.901 --> 37:13.236
and asterisks next to the high-ticket items,

37:13.238 --> 37:15.238
so it's clear which ones they're
gonna try to fence first,

37:15.240 --> 37:18.457
'cause they're super, super valuable.

37:18.493 --> 37:21.160
So you're gonna want to get
this list out to pawnshops,

37:21.212 --> 37:24.580
uh, collectors, question anyone who's done

37:24.582 --> 37:26.249
any sort of crime like this in the past.

37:26.301 --> 37:29.218
You know, the... the usual suspects.

37:29.254 --> 37:32.088
Uh, can I get you the list
so you can start investigating?

37:32.090 --> 37:34.173
Yeah, you... Yeah,
if you could get us that list...

37:34.225 --> 37:36.342
Okay, I'll... I'll print it out.

37:36.394 --> 37:40.346
Hank Aaron, mint.
God, my signed Derek Jeter.

37:40.398 --> 37:42.648
Willie Mays, O-Pee-Chee.

37:42.684 --> 37:45.184
Got to breathe. Just keep breathing.

37:45.236 --> 37:46.319
Keep breathing.

37:46.354 --> 37:48.521
- Okay.
- I know, right?

37:48.573 --> 37:50.406
- Left the TV.
- Uh-huh.

37:50.441 --> 37:52.775
- Left the computer.
- Right.

37:54.913 --> 37:56.145
Huh.

38:02.420 --> 38:04.320
There's something wrong with this picture.

38:10.428 --> 38:12.878
[Printer whirring in distance]

38:37.989 --> 38:39.655
[Flashlight clicks]

38:50.501 --> 38:51.834
[Sighs]

38:54.005 --> 38:55.888
[Flashlight clicks]

39:18.598 --> 39:20.599
[Sighs]

39:22.883 --> 39:25.383
[Dialing]

39:29.707 --> 39:31.340
Hey, it's me.

39:31.376 --> 39:33.709
Another perfect day in paradise out here.

39:33.711 --> 39:34.961
I'm in the pool.

39:35.013 --> 39:38.214
Okay, call me.

39:38.216 --> 39:40.716
[Cellphone beeps]

39:53.898 --> 39:56.732
- Hi! How are you?
- Hey, babe. Did you get lunch?

39:56.734 --> 39:58.151
WOMAN: I did.

39:58.203 --> 39:59.986
MAN: You know, I think
I'm burning up back here.

40:00.038 --> 40:01.788
Oh, really? Well, you're just in luck.

40:01.823 --> 40:03.406
- Look what I have.
- Oh, hey, great.

40:07.412 --> 40:09.245
Oh, yeah, you're all red back here.

40:09.247 --> 40:11.631
Yeah. That feels good, babe.

40:11.666 --> 40:13.442
- [Dialing]
- I told you not to

40:13.454 --> 40:15.229
spend so much time in the sun.

40:15.253 --> 40:17.970
You don't listen.

40:18.006 --> 40:19.922
Yeah, it's me again.

40:19.924 --> 40:24.060
Listen, as I speak,
not 25 feet away from me,

40:24.095 --> 40:27.313
I'm looking at <i>the</i> mark.

40:27.348 --> 40:31.100
Think Thurston Howell III
if he shacked up with Ginger.

40:31.102 --> 40:33.169
[Chuckles] He's dripping in Gucci.

40:33.204 --> 40:35.338
It's like I'm at the watering hole,

40:35.373 --> 40:38.357
and I'm watching the fattest,
slowest water buffalo

40:38.409 --> 40:42.778
expose his neck to me, and
I'm the lioness ready to strike.

40:42.780 --> 40:45.114
[Chuckles] Come, Kim.

40:45.116 --> 40:49.368
Join me. Join the pride.

40:51.456 --> 40:53.372
Um, I said "lioness"

40:53.424 --> 40:56.175
because it's the females
who do all the hunting.

40:56.211 --> 40:59.462
Uh, just wanted to be species-accurate,

40:59.464 --> 41:00.963
irrespective of my own sex.

41:00.965 --> 41:03.549
It's a <i>National Geographic</i> thing. Anyway...

41:03.601 --> 41:06.219
Get out here.

41:06.271 --> 41:07.687
Bye.

41:07.722 --> 41:10.223
[Cellphone beeps]

41:12.277 --> 41:14.777
[Lawnmower running in distance]

41:20.568 --> 41:23.069
[Chuckles]

41:41.839 --> 41:44.340
[Dialing]

41:50.765 --> 41:52.682
Santa Fe, New Mexico.

41:52.684 --> 41:56.852
I need the number
of a law firm... Davis & Main.

41:56.854 --> 42:00.690
Yeah, you can connect me.

43:28.279 --> 43:31.580
[Indistinct conversations]

43:33.618 --> 43:35.835
[Telephone rings in distance]

43:35.870 --> 43:37.586
WOMAN: Davis & Main.

43:37.622 --> 43:41.340
OMAR: There are a few options
on the company cars.

43:41.376 --> 43:43.426
We can arrange a test-drive
whenever you'd like.

43:43.461 --> 43:45.378
Company car... wow.

43:45.430 --> 43:48.047
And there's a service that will
deliver it right to you,

43:48.099 --> 43:49.515
wherever you want.

43:49.550 --> 43:51.100
And if you find you're not happy with it,

43:51.135 --> 43:53.052
it's not a big deal to change it out.

43:53.104 --> 43:55.354
That sounds really, uh...

43:55.390 --> 43:57.440
[Sighs] Yeah.

44:05.199 --> 44:07.900
This is, uh, interesting.

44:07.952 --> 44:09.318
Oh, if, uh... [Chuckles]

44:09.320 --> 44:11.454
If this isn't to your taste,

44:11.489 --> 44:13.406
we have a collection of art in-house

44:13.458 --> 44:15.041
you can, uh, choose from.

44:15.076 --> 44:16.059
Anytime you're ready,

44:16.133 --> 44:17.432
I can put together some
samples for you to review.

44:17.995 --> 44:20.713
I... I... No, I like this.

44:20.748 --> 44:25.384
Good. Uh, well, any other needs
you have, I'm here to help.

44:25.420 --> 44:27.586
Office supplies, dietary needs...

44:27.638 --> 44:30.556
Anything special you want
stocked in the fridge?

44:30.591 --> 44:34.009
Uh, maybe a humidifier?
Gets kind of dry in here.

44:34.011 --> 44:36.896
Omar, I... I'm pretty low-maintenance.

44:36.931 --> 44:39.849
Sure. Well, if there's anything you need,

44:39.851 --> 44:41.934
I'm right outside the door.

44:41.986 --> 44:43.986
Great.

44:44.021 --> 44:45.738
If I think of anything.

44:45.773 --> 44:48.908
Good.

44:48.943 --> 44:51.327
Hey, do you think, um...

44:51.362 --> 44:52.912
I'm just looking at this.

44:52.947 --> 44:55.798
D-Do we get a choice of desks?

44:55.833 --> 44:57.366
What were you thinking?

44:57.368 --> 45:02.371
Um... is it possible, um...

45:02.373 --> 45:05.758
Can we do... cocobolo?

45:05.793 --> 45:08.427
Cocobolo desk? Absolutely.

45:08.463 --> 45:10.629
I'll get right on that.

45:10.681 --> 45:13.182
[Chuckles]

45:19.190 --> 45:22.391
[Indistinct conversations in distance]

